    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Large units of building material made from a mixture of cement and an aggregate, usually 8 x 16 inches and of various thicknesses.  A mixture of cement, aggregate, and water is vibrated and compacted in steel molds and then cured in air, steam, or under autoclaving processes. Became a very popular building material beginning in the early 20th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
